# Shrimp Market Size, Share, Industry Trends, Forecast, 2032
## Introduction
The global shrimp market size was USD 40.35 billion in 2023 and is projected to grow from USD 42.90 billion in 2024 to USD 74.24 billion by 2032 at a CAGR of 7.09% during the 2024-2032 period.

## Key Market Insights
* The global shrimp market size was USD 40.35 billion in 2023 and is projected to grow from USD 42.90 billion in 2024 to USD 74.24 billion by 2032 at a CAGR of 7.09% during the 2024-2032 period.
* Asia Pacific dominated the shrimp market with a market share of 38.22% in 2023.
* The shrimp market size in the U.S. is projected to grow significantly, reaching an estimated value of USD 12.10 billion by 2032, driven by increasing popularity of seafood as a good protein source and the adoption of flexitarian diets in the country.

## SHRIMP Industry Landscape Overview
### Market Size & Forecast
* 2023 Market Size: USD 40.35 billion
* 2024 Market Size: USD 42.90 billion
* 2032 Forecast Market Size: USD 74.24 billion
* CAGR: 7.09% (2024–2032)

### Market Share
* Asia Pacific dominated the shrimp market with a 38.22% share in 2023, led by strong aquaculture growth, seafood demand, and traditional consumption in countries like China, India, and Vietnam.
* The U.S. shrimp market is projected to reach USD 12.10 billion by 2032, driven by the growing popularity of seafood as a protein source and the rise of flexitarian diets.

## Key Country Highlights
* United States: Shrimp consumption is rising due to the adoption of high-protein and flexitarian diets; NOAA supports sustainable fisheries and anti-IUU fishing practices, aiding market growth.
* Asia Pacific: Largest shrimp producer globally; regional production and exports drive the market despite temporary setbacks during the COVID-19 pandemic; major contributors include India, China, and Vietnam.
* Europe: Slower growth due to preference for other seafood (e.g., salmon, cod), though demand for white and brown shrimp from APAC creates import opportunities.
* South America: Stable growth, led by Ecuador as a major producer and exporter; shrimp farming developments in Brazil and Argentina offer expansion potential.
* Middle East & Africa: Market at an early growth stage; demand for white shrimp is rising among middle-income consumers, supporting steady growth.

## Shrimp Market Trends
* New Trend of Adapting to Flexitarians Lifestyle to Increase Demand for Shrimps
* Innovations in the seafood sector have been continuously growing in the last few years.

## Shrimp Market Growth Factors
* Sustainable Seafood Choices and More Focus on Adding High Protein Drive Market Growth
* Globalization of Regional Products and the Rise of Online Sales

## Restraining Factors
* Trade War between Developed Economies Restraints the Growth of the Market

## Shrimp Market Segmentation Analysis
### By Type Analysis
* White Shrimp Segment Holds the Major Market Share Attributed to its Consumption in all Regions & Easy Availability
* Brown decapod crustaceans are expected to showcase promising growth because of their growing consumption in Asian countries.

### By Form Analysis
* Frozen Shrimp to Hold Major Market Share owing to its Availability in Major Supermarkets/Hypermarkets and Online Platforms
* Canned seafood is preserved using added preservatives, and they are kept fresh with added texture-enhancing ingredients that attract the consumers.

### By End-user Analysis
* Commercial Segment to Lead Owing to Growing Consumption of Seafood in Restaurants
* Apart from the increase in the commercial segment, there is a strong CAGR expected in the household segment in the global market.

### By Distribution Channel Analysis
* Change in Consumers Shopping Pattern from Traditional to Online Channels to add Stimulus to the Growth
* The specialty store segment among the various distribution channels for shrimp products sales is dominating the market.

## Regional Insights
* Asia Pacific Shrimp Market Size, 2023 (USD Billion)
* North America is expected to grow with steady growth rate majorly due to the rising demand for brown shrimps and big-sized decapod crustaceans in this region.
* Europe is expected to grow with a slower growth compared to North America.
* The South American decapod crustaceans market is projected to witness stable growth.
* The market for decapod crustaceans in the Middle East and Africa is still at the initial stage.

